{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''frog''' (plural: [[frogs]])

# a small hopping [[amphibian]]
# a [[fastener]] for clothing consisting of a [[button]] that fits through a [[loop]].
# the end of a violin [[bow]] that the violinist holds.
#(Cockney rhyming slang) [[Road]]. Shorter, more common form of [[frog and toad]].
# (''British, derogatory'') a [[French]] person (adjective [[froggy]]).
# the depression in the upper face of a pressed or handmade clay brick
# a part of a turnout on a railway where there tracks cross and make a lot of noise like a frog.
# an organ on the bottom of a [[horse]]'s [[hoof]] that assists in the circulation of [[blood]]

